# zget Gap Solutions: Deep Implementation Plan

> **Research Date**: January 3, 2026
> **Status**: Proposed

---

## Gap 1: Missing Service Worker (Incomplete PWA)

### The Problem
Without a Service Worker, the PWA has no offline capability, no background sync, and no asset caching. This means:
- Users can't access their library when offline
- Every page load requires a network fetch
- The "Add to Home Screen" experience is degraded

### The Solution: Workbox + Stale-While-Revalidate

**Workbox** is Google's production-ready Service Worker library. It abstracts away the complexity of cache management.

#### Strategy

| Resource Type | Caching Strategy | Rationale |
|---------------|------------------|-----------|
| App Shell (HTML, CSS, JS) | **Precache** | Instant load on first visit |
| Thumbnails | **Cache-First** | Rarely change, optimize for speed |
| API responses (`/api/library`) | **Stale-While-Revalidate** | Show cached data immediately, update in background |
| Video files | **Network-Only** | Too large to cache, stream on demand |

#### Implementation

**1. Create `service-worker.js`**
```javascript
import { precacheAndRoute } from 'workbox-precaching';
import { registerRoute } from 'workbox-routing';
import { StaleWhileRevalidate, CacheFirst } from 'workbox-strategies';
import { ExpirationPlugin } from 'workbox-expiration';

// Precache app shell
precacheAndRoute(self.__WB_MANIFEST);

// Thumbnails: Cache-First (30 day expiry)
registerRoute(
  ({ url }) => url.pathname.startsWith('/api/thumbnails'),
  new CacheFirst({
    cacheName: 'thumbnails-cache',
    plugins: [
      new ExpirationPlugin({ maxEntries: 500, maxAgeSeconds: 30 * 24 * 60 * 60 }),
    ],
  })
);

// Library API: Stale-While-Revalidate
registerRoute(
  ({ url }) => url.pathname === '/api/library',
  new StaleWhileRevalidate({ cacheName: 'api-cache' })
);

// Offline fallback
self.addEventListener('fetch', (event) => {
  if (event.request.mode === 'navigate') {
    event.respondWith(
      fetch(event.request).catch(() => caches.match('/offline.html'))
    );
  }
});
```

**2. Register in [index.html](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/index.html)**
```javascript
if ('serviceWorker' in navigator) {
  navigator.serviceWorker.register('/service-worker.js');
}
```

**3. Create `offline.html`** — simple fallback page

#### Effort Estimate
**~4-6 hours** to implement and test.

---

## Gap 2: Monolithic Frontend (1,281 lines)

### The Problem
A single [index.html](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/index.html) with 1,281 lines is:
- Hard to navigate and maintain
- Impossible to test individual components
- Prone to merge conflicts in team settings
- Violates separation of concerns

### The Solution: Web Components (Native)

Web Components are browser-native and require **no framework or build step**. They provide:
- **Custom Elements**: Define your own HTML tags
- **Shadow DOM**: Encapsulate styles (no CSS leaks)
- **ES Modules**: Import/export for code organization

#### Proposed Component Structure

```
src/zget/server/static/
├── index.html           # Shell only (~100 lines)
├── styles/
│   └── main.css         # Extracted global styles
├── components/
│   ├── vault-view.js    # <zget-vault>
│   ├── regions-view.js  # <zget-regions>
│   ├── settings-view.js # <zget-settings>
│   ├── video-player.js  # <zget-player>
│   └── stats-bar.js     # <zget-stats>
├── service-worker.js    # (from Gap 1)
└── offline.html
```

#### Example: `<zget-vault>` Component

```javascript
// components/vault-view.js
class ZgetVault extends HTMLElement {
  constructor() {
    super();
    this.attachShadow({ mode: 'open' });
    this.videos = [];
  }

  connectedCallback() {
    this.render();
    this.fetchLibrary();
  }

  async fetchLibrary() {
    const response = await fetch('/api/library');
    this.videos = await response.json();
    this.render();
  }

  render() {
    this.shadowRoot.innerHTML = `
      <style>
        :host { display: block; }
        /* Component-scoped styles */
      </style>
      <div class="vault-container">
        ${this.videos.map(v => this.renderVideo(v)).join('')}
      </div>
    `;
  }

  renderVideo(v) {
    return `<div class="library-item">${v.title}</div>`;
  }
}

customElements.define('zget-vault', ZgetVault);
```

#### Usage in [index.html](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/index.html)
```html
<script type="module" src="/components/vault-view.js"></script>
<zget-vault></zget-vault>
```

#### Migration Strategy
1. Extract CSS to `styles/main.css`
2. Create component files one at a time
3. Replace sections in [index.html](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/index.html) with custom elements
4. Test each component in isolation

#### Effort Estimate
**~8-12 hours** for full migration.

